5.18.20  6:16 pm   hello, i am a 19 year old girl. Songs have been known to write themselves in my head since I started thinking, but the past few days I have written 2 or 3 songs a day. my head feels full of songs. but I am always more interested in writing a new song than I am producing a song I've already written. Should i fight myself to produce the old songs or should I just go with the flow and not think about it?

      keep them all in a list. be sure to document them well (with charts/demos, whatever you need to be sure how it goes. you can't expect to 'remember' because they are brand new songs). let the list grow until it's out of control. when you feel like you can't take it anymore, i have some tips for how to turn the boat around, into selection and production. but for now, enjoy writing. make other people jealous of how many songs you have in the bank

5.18.20  5:49 pm   I think I understand "changing keys" a little better now. Basically you play a chord that "means" one thing in the previous key, but means something else in the new key, so the listener follows the chord thinking it belongs to the previous key but surprise! it leads them somewhere else. If you'll forgive me the crude approximation, it's a little bit like a "your mom" joke, in that the same words suddenly get a whole new context. Am I making any sense? I'm sure there's a lot more to it, so if you've got any wise words I'm listening. Thanks!

     that is one way to change keys. but sometimes you can also do it with no pivot
